sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant AuthServer as Authorization Server
    participant ResourceServer as Resource Server

    Note over Client, ResourceServer: OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code Flow with PKCE

    Client->>Client: Generate code_verifier and code_challenge
    Client->>Browser: Redirect to /authorize with client_id, redirect_uri, scope, code_challenge
    Browser->>AuthServer: GET /authorize
    AuthServer->>Browser: Show login page (if not authenticated)
    Browser->>AuthServer: User credentials
    AuthServer->>Browser: Show consent page
    Browser->>AuthServer: User grants consent
    AuthServer->>Browser: Redirect to redirect_uri with authorization_code
    Browser->>Client: Return authorization_code
    Client->>AuthServer: POST /token with authorization_code, code_verifier, client_id
    AuthServer->>AuthServer: Validate authorization_code and code_verifier
    AuthServer->>Client: Return access_token, refresh_token, id_token
    Client->>ResourceServer: API request with access_token
    ResourceServer->>AuthServer: Validate access_token (introspection or JWT verify)
    AuthServer->>ResourceServer: Token validation response
    ResourceServer->>Client: API response
    
    Note over Client, AuthServer: Token refresh when access_token expires
    Client->>AuthServer: POST /token with refresh_token
    AuthServer->>Client: Return new access_token

